Author: Alright#0419
Content:
`-splitperc=100` in startup params or `setstakingsplit 100` rpc command will combine the utxo used to stake a block with the coinbase entirely. 

a value of 50 will send 50% of the utxo used to stake the block to coinbase transaction

Author: Alright#0419
Content: make sense?

Author: Alright#0419
Content: have some docs, will get them up soon

Author: Alright#0419
Content: basically, `splitperc=100` is what pos64staker does

Author: Alright#0419
Content: `splitperc=0` (the default) is what we're used to

Author: Alright#0419
Content: oh a value of 100 isn't quite the same as what pos64staker does, it will merge it to the coinbase address

Author: Alright#0419
Content: so recommended to not use -pubkey with `splitperc=100`. If you do, all your utxos will end up in `-pubkey` address eventually
